main event: Two objects were observed in the sky over the Grand Canyon National Park in Arizona on August 23, 1965 around 5:07 AM to 5:11 AM.
interesting points: The objects appeared from the west, with a larger or brighter object leading, followed by a smaller and not so bright object.
The objects remained in sight for approximately 4 minutes before disappearing into the brightness of the dawn sky.
The Air Force evaluated the sighting and suggested the objects could have been space debris or high-flying aircraft.
The objects were observed at an altitude of 30-35 degrees above the horizon and were traveling from west to east.
The Air Force requested additional information through the U.A.C.I. to determine what the objects could have been.
sighted object: two objects, one larger or brighter leading the other smaller and less bright
